WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:11.250 --> 00:00:13.916
Let's begin near the end.

2
00:00:14.666 --> 00:00:17.500
The final act of a tragic story.

3
00:00:18.666 --> 00:00:22.208
When you've seen as many wars
as I have. you get used to it.

4
00:00:22.833 --> 00:00:26.666
The hard part is watching
worlds fall that don't need to

5
00:00:27.250 --> 00:00:30.124
because a hero can no longer
rise to meet their moment.

6
00:00:30.125 --> 00:00:31.208
[metal footsteps]

7
00:00:32.750 --> 00:00:34.249
[sighs]

8
00:00:34.250 --> 00:00:38.541
But I swore an oath.
And so I watch.

9
00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:46.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

10
00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:03.958
<i>In every variation
of this universe.</i>

11
00:01:04.750 --> 00:01:07.416
<i>Riri Williams is
its last best hope.</i>

12
00:01:11.666 --> 00:01:14.458
<i>But in every one I've watched.</i>

13
00:01:15.083 --> 00:01:18.958
<i>no matter how hard she fights.
and how long she struggles.</i>

14
00:01:20.125 --> 00:01:21.750
<i>she always fails.</i>

15
00:01:23.708 --> 00:01:24.750
<i>Always.</i>

16
00:01:36.416 --> 00:01:37.416
You're late.

17
00:01:37.916 --> 00:01:39.125
[Riri] Patrols are everywhere.

18
00:01:40.166 --> 00:01:43.249
And I'm not exactly popular
with the Iron Federation. so...

19
00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:45.916
Well. blowing up their
convoys probably didn't help.

20
00:01:46.458 --> 00:01:47.458
You have the money?

21
00:01:48.041 --> 00:01:49.250
You have my score?

22
00:01:50.458 --> 00:01:53.291
Strictly analog.
just like you asked.

23
00:01:55.041 --> 00:01:58.625
This looks intact. How
many more can you get me?

24
00:01:59.291 --> 00:02:00.415
You're willing to risk a lot

25
00:02:00.416 --> 00:02:02.625
for someone who doesn't
strike me as the baking type.

26
00:02:03.541 --> 00:02:04.791
Unless the rumors are true.

27
00:02:05.291 --> 00:02:07.290
and what you're really
cooking up is a weapon.

28
00:02:07.291 --> 00:02:09.041
I don't know what
you're talking about.

29
00:02:09.708 --> 00:02:11.250
I'm just looking to
make a Bundt cake.

30
00:02:12.458 --> 00:02:13.999
Tread carefully. Williams.

31
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:17.416
'Cause once the Federation has you
in its sights. the story's over.

32
00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:20.583
[distant whirring. footsteps]

33
00:02:21.750 --> 00:02:22.833
Nothing personal.

34
00:02:23.833 --> 00:02:25.124
It's just business.

35
00:02:25.125 --> 00:02:27.875
Yeah. well. that's the problem
with everyone these days.

36
00:02:28.416 --> 00:02:30.208
You never know who's
real and who's a fake.

37
00:02:33.916 --> 00:02:35.125
[pulsing. glass shatters]

38
00:02:37.333 --> 00:02:38.333
[Riri Williams grunts]

39
00:02:40.833 --> 00:02:42.833
Come on. come on.
Why won't it start?

40
00:02:47.916 --> 00:02:49.958
Fake! Fake!

41
00:02:50.541 --> 00:02:51.874
Aah!

42
00:02:51.875 --> 00:02:53.291
Guess that one was real.

43
00:02:54.666 --> 00:02:56.791
- Y'all keepin' it real. too? Bingo.
- [pinging]

44
00:02:59.458 --> 00:03:00.958
Come on! Come on!

45
00:03:04.875 --> 00:03:07.250
- Come on! Come on. just start.
- [sputtering]

46
00:03:11.166 --> 00:03:12.625
[screaming]

47
00:03:15.416 --> 00:03:17.416
[groans]

48
00:03:19.333 --> 00:03:21.708
[clanging. powering down]

49
00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:33.040
Please be a hologram.
Please be a hologram.

50
00:03:33.041 --> 00:03:34.583
[screams. groans]

51
00:03:36.083 --> 00:03:38.333
[strains] Okay. I guess not.

52
00:03:39.375 --> 00:03:40.500
[choking]

53
00:03:41.791 --> 00:03:42.916
[screams]

54
00:03:43.958 --> 00:03:46.124
[thuds. groans]

55
00:03:46.125 --> 00:03:48.957
Who are you people? What
the hell is goin' on?

56
00:03:48.958 --> 00:03:51.500
I'm Admiral Ying Nan
with the Alliance.

57
00:03:53.125 --> 00:03:55.500
He is coming about.
Mystic support!

58
00:03:57.583 --> 00:03:59.333
Captain Valkyrie. let's move.

59
00:04:04.333 --> 00:04:06.625
[The Watcher] <i>Welcome to Earth.</i>

60
00:04:08.375 --> 00:04:10.166
<i>What's left of it anyway.</i>

61
00:04:17.041 --> 00:04:18.083
[The Watcher] <i>Time.</i>

62
00:04:21.541 --> 00:04:22.625
<i>Space.</i>

63
00:04:24.375 --> 00:04:25.416
<i>Reality.</i>

64
00:04:28.291 --> 00:04:29.958
<i>It's more than a linear path.</i>

65
00:04:34.833 --> 00:04:39.333
<i>It's a prism of
endless possibility.</i>

66
00:04:41.875 --> 00:04:45.291
<i>where a single choice can branch
out into infinite realities.</i>

67
00:04:48.083 --> 00:04:50.833
<i>creating alternate worlds
from the ones you know.</i>

68
00:04:54.958 --> 00:04:56.291
<i>I am the Watcher.</i>

69
00:04:58.541 --> 00:05:01.708
<i>I am your guide through
these vast new realities.</i>

70
00:05:03.125 --> 00:05:06.625
<i>Follow me and ponder
the question...</i>

71
00:05:10.291 --> 00:05:11.916
<i>"What if?"</i>

72
00:05:17.625 --> 00:05:21.332
<i>The end of the world began
with a birth of the Celestial</i>

73
00:05:21.333 --> 00:05:24.041
<i>that had been gestating
deep beneath the surface.</i>

74
00:05:25.708 --> 00:05:27.290
<i>In this universe.</i>

75
00:05:27.291 --> 00:05:31.625
<i>the Emergence occurred years before
the Eternals could unite to stop it.</i>

76
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.958
<i>But one man saw the
chaos as an opportunity.</i>

77
00:05:37.708 --> 00:05:40.957
<i>The brilliant but ego-maniacal
engineer. Quentin Beck.</i>

78
00:05:40.958 --> 00:05:43.166
<i>who took over Stark Industries.</i>

79
00:05:43.708 --> 00:05:46.207
<i>What followed was a
long and protracted war</i>

80
00:05:46.208 --> 00:05:50.791
<i>between an alliance of resistance
fighters and Beck's Iron Federation.</i>

81
00:05:51.291 --> 00:05:53.208
<i>And with victory
within his grasp.</i>

82
00:05:53.750 --> 00:05:59.416
<i>Beck was determined to ensure the Alliance
took its last breath before he did.</i>

83
00:06:00.166 --> 00:06:01.166
[breathing heavily]

84
00:06:02.166 --> 00:06:05.791
The Alliance is down
to their last brigade.

85
00:06:08.166 --> 00:06:09.500
Go to their base

86
00:06:10.625 --> 00:06:12.083
and end them.

87
00:06:20.458 --> 00:06:21.958
[breathing heavily]

88
00:06:43.208 --> 00:06:45.708
We pick up all kinds of
stuff floating around here.

89
00:06:47.666 --> 00:06:49.458
- Drink?
- [exhales]

90
00:06:50.291 --> 00:06:53.625
This used to be someone's.
and now it's just...

91
00:06:55.458 --> 00:06:56.458
wreckage.

92
00:07:00.750 --> 00:07:02.916
Hard to see what we
have to drink to.

93
00:07:03.791 --> 00:07:04.958
We are still here.

94
00:07:05.916 --> 00:07:09.791
After the Emergence. that
seems as good a reason as any.

95
00:07:10.375 --> 00:07:12.291
So why am I here?

96
00:07:12.833 --> 00:07:15.624
Or did y'all go through all this
trouble just to make me feel special?

97
00:07:15.625 --> 00:07:16.832
[chuckles]

98
00:07:16.833 --> 00:07:18.249
Our ears on the ground say

99
00:07:18.250 --> 00:07:20.624
the magnetron you acquired
from the Power Broker

100
00:07:20.625 --> 00:07:23.125
is for a weapon of
great interest to us.

101
00:07:24.041 --> 00:07:26.625
A weapon to destroy the Vision.

102
00:07:27.958 --> 00:07:30.207
So. what. you've
been spying on me?

103
00:07:30.208 --> 00:07:31.374
Yes.

104
00:07:31.375 --> 00:07:33.082
- For a long time. actually.
- [sighs]

105
00:07:33.083 --> 00:07:34.999
Our intel indicates

106
00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:39.082
your weapon powers down
Vibranium. decouples it.

107
00:07:39.083 --> 00:07:42.832
But to take out a synthezoid.
you are going to need

108
00:07:42.833 --> 00:07:47.458
a lot more than one busted
part from a Kiddy Cake Cooker.

109
00:07:48.541 --> 00:07:51.124
Wow. okay. Y'all really
have been spying on me.

110
00:07:51.125 --> 00:07:53.666
We just saved your life.
I think you can trust us.

111
00:07:54.541 --> 00:07:55.791
[Riri] Well. that's the thing.

112
00:07:56.208 --> 00:07:57.416
I don't trust anyone.

113
00:07:58.791 --> 00:08:01.500
And from what I've heard. the
Alliance is kind of a sinking ship.

114
00:08:02.250 --> 00:08:04.916
Hmm. Well. you are
right about that one.

115
00:08:05.500 --> 00:08:07.875
Our ship sank a long time ago.

116
00:08:27.458 --> 00:08:30.250
The Vision has ravaged our
forces across the Federation.

117
00:08:30.833 --> 00:08:33.874
This base is all that
remains of the Alliance.

118
00:08:33.875 --> 00:08:37.207
Just when you thought things
couldn't get any more hopeless.

119
00:08:37.208 --> 00:08:39.125
The planet may have
been destroyed.

120
00:08:40.125 --> 00:08:41.791
but the world carries on.

121
00:08:42.333 --> 00:08:44.832
What you decide to
make of the pieces...

122
00:08:44.833 --> 00:08:47.874
- [opens]
- well. that is up to you.

123
00:08:47.875 --> 00:08:50.040
Damn. this is...

124
00:08:50.041 --> 00:08:51.415
[Ying Nan] Everything?

125
00:08:51.416 --> 00:08:54.750
Everything you will need
to build your weapon.

126
00:08:55.333 --> 00:08:57.958
That is. of course.
if you're interested.

127
00:08:58.541 --> 00:09:01.374
A lot of people died
for all of this.

128
00:09:01.375 --> 00:09:04.916
If you really think there is
no hope left in this world.

129
00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:07.250
then make some yourself.

130
00:09:09.208 --> 00:09:10.333
Y'all got any snacks?

131
00:09:10.916 --> 00:09:12.999
I work better with brain food.

132
00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.624
- [chuckles]
- [man] <i>Admiral. we have incoming.</i>

133
00:09:15.625 --> 00:09:17.165
What's the molecular density?

134
00:09:17.166 --> 00:09:19.999
- [man] <i>Reads as variable.
- </i> [sighs]

135
00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:22.332
[Ying Nan] Eyes up. everyone!
Secure the perimeter!

136
00:09:22.333 --> 00:09:24.540
<i>- Nothing gets through to the lab.</i>
- [soldier 1] Let's go.

137
00:09:24.541 --> 00:09:26.749
- [soldier 2] Go. go. go!
- Two by two. two by two.

138
00:09:26.750 --> 00:09:29.833
[indistinct chatter]

139
00:09:50.500 --> 00:09:52.249
He is already here.

140
00:09:52.250 --> 00:09:53.374
[Valkyrie] <i>Copy that.</i>

141
00:09:53.375 --> 00:09:55.624
How long do you think you'll
need to build that weapon?

142
00:09:55.625 --> 00:09:57.499
- About 12 hours.
- Hah!

143
00:09:57.500 --> 00:09:58.999
Well. how long do I have?

144
00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:00.499
Seven-and-a-half minutes.

145
00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:02.165
I'm sorry. what?

146
00:10:02.166 --> 00:10:05.665
That's how long the Vishanti
protection spell is going to hold.

147
00:10:05.666 --> 00:10:07.333
No. What? What?

148
00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:19.750
[gunfire. man screaming]

149
00:10:25.875 --> 00:10:27.124
[grunting]

150
00:10:27.125 --> 00:10:28.625
[ricochets]

151
00:10:32.416 --> 00:10:34.916
Seven-and-a-half
minutes. Really? Really?

152
00:10:48.458 --> 00:10:49.458
[thuds]

153
00:10:54.708 --> 00:10:55.916
[Wong] Sorry. Casper.

154
00:10:57.333 --> 00:11:00.625
You're not getting through. At
least not for the next five minutes.

155
00:11:01.166 --> 00:11:02.583
[Valkyrie. Ying Nan scream]

156
00:11:06.916 --> 00:11:09.874
Guess I need to be an
engineer and a magician. Cool.

157
00:11:09.875 --> 00:11:11.083
[both continue screaming]

158
00:11:12.500 --> 00:11:16.166
Just building a totally theoretical
weapon on the fly. What could go wrong?

159
00:11:17.750 --> 00:11:19.165
[grunting]

160
00:11:19.166 --> 00:11:21.666
Come on. Come on. Come on.

161
00:11:25.583 --> 00:11:26.583
[Wong screams]

162
00:11:33.666 --> 00:11:35.582
[Riri] Cool. cool!
Tick tock. Riri!

163
00:11:35.583 --> 00:11:37.665
In seven-and-a-half minutes.

164
00:11:37.666 --> 00:11:39.999
You can't grill a hamburger
in seven-and-a-half minutes.

165
00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:41.083
but sure. fine!

166
00:11:41.791 --> 00:11:44.708
Come on. Come on. Come on!

167
00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:50.500
Yeah. Yeah. come at me.
you dead-eyed son of a...

168
00:11:51.250 --> 00:11:52.249
What?

169
00:11:52.250 --> 00:11:55.000
No. no. no. no. no. come
on. come on. let's go!

170
00:11:55.500 --> 00:11:57.540
Increase the frequency
wave. reverse the polarity.

171
00:11:57.541 --> 00:11:59.375
- Come on. let's go!
- [charging. pulses]

172
00:12:09.833 --> 00:12:12.375
[gasps] You did it.

173
00:12:15.083 --> 00:12:16.290
Without his guard dog.

174
00:12:16.291 --> 00:12:19.249
Beck's illusions are gonna
have a lot less bite.

175
00:12:19.250 --> 00:12:22.749
Perhaps there's a little hope
left in this world after all.

176
00:12:22.750 --> 00:12:24.665
Good. we will need it.

177
00:12:24.666 --> 00:12:27.457
This location has
been compromised.

178
00:12:27.458 --> 00:12:31.458
We will need to wipe away any last
traces of our operation and move out.

179
00:12:32.041 --> 00:12:33.625
What about the rest of the crew?

180
00:12:36.375 --> 00:12:38.625
[Ying Nan] He killed them all.

181
00:12:44.375 --> 00:12:49.040
<i>Reverse the polarity. Come on. let's move!
Reverse the polarity. Come on. let's move!</i>

182
00:12:49.041 --> 00:12:52.332
<i>Reverse the polarity. Come on. let's
move! Reverse the polarity. Come on...</i>

183
00:12:52.333 --> 00:12:55.915
[Beck] This shouldn't
be possible! [coughing]

184
00:12:55.916 --> 00:12:57.916
<i>Reverse the polarity.
Come on. let's move!</i>

185
00:13:00.291 --> 00:13:04.125
Who the hell is Riri Williams?

186
00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:11.583
[Ying Nan] Our fallen
allies came from many lands.

187
00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:14.583
but they united for one cause.

188
00:13:16.583 --> 00:13:21.750
May their sacrifice be a light
of hope seen across the stars.

189
00:13:23.333 --> 00:13:25.458
- Light the fuse.
- Mm.

190
00:13:29.125 --> 00:13:30.125
[crackling]

191
00:14:03.083 --> 00:14:04.666
Where's Riri?

192
00:14:16.416 --> 00:14:18.291
[The Watcher]
She's lost so much.

193
00:14:19.041 --> 00:14:23.666
Friends. family. the
world she once knew.

194
00:14:28.958 --> 00:14:31.708
<i>She's clung to this
fight to sustain her.</i>

195
00:14:32.541 --> 00:14:36.000
<i>But in the end. it will be
the fight that kills her.</i>

196
00:14:39.750 --> 00:14:41.125
As it always does.

197
00:14:50.375 --> 00:14:51.791
The Vision news
has spooked Beck.

198
00:14:52.375 --> 00:14:56.291
He's reinforcing his Iron Legion on
every province in the Federation.

199
00:14:56.833 --> 00:14:58.874
Any chatter on the
encrypted channels?

200
00:14:58.875 --> 00:15:02.916
Dead silence. We are
all that is left.

201
00:15:04.083 --> 00:15:07.957
Hmm. Well. it's only a matter of
time before Beck finds us. too.

202
00:15:07.958 --> 00:15:11.500
So we take the fight to him while
we're still here and finish him.

203
00:15:12.541 --> 00:15:14.749
With Vision gone. Beck
has never been weaker.

204
00:15:14.750 --> 00:15:18.916
The illusion network is all he has
left. I say we take that from him. too.

205
00:15:19.500 --> 00:15:21.291
What exactly are you proposing?

206
00:15:21.833 --> 00:15:24.999
Beck's entire operation is
run on a nanotech network.

207
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:27.290
To take it down. we need
to drop behind enemy lines.

208
00:15:27.291 --> 00:15:30.833
blow the nanites powering his
illusions. and then it's over.

209
00:15:31.333 --> 00:15:32.791
His reign. his terror.

210
00:15:33.625 --> 00:15:34.665
Him.

211
00:15:34.666 --> 00:15:36.707
His headquarters are located

212
00:15:36.708 --> 00:15:41.665
on a planetary fragment on the
fast side of the asteroid ring.

213
00:15:41.666 --> 00:15:44.749
Even if we were to
survive the approach...

214
00:15:44.750 --> 00:15:47.040
A base like that will
be heavily guarded.

215
00:15:47.041 --> 00:15:49.666
We'd be entering a world of
illusions completely blind.

216
00:15:50.291 --> 00:15:51.833
I can get us past the illusions.

217
00:15:52.416 --> 00:15:55.374
I can plug myself into the
system running Beck's holograms.

218
00:15:55.375 --> 00:15:56.749
Such technology...

219
00:15:56.750 --> 00:15:58.125
Is impossible.

220
00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:00.333
But not for Riri.

221
00:16:01.416 --> 00:16:03.291
It's a big swing. no doubt.

222
00:16:03.791 --> 00:16:05.832
That's why you
gotta have vision.

223
00:16:05.833 --> 00:16:09.416
And wouldn't you know. I
got all his spare parts.

224
00:16:10.125 --> 00:16:12.500
[The Watcher sighs]
Here we go again.

225
00:16:20.541 --> 00:16:24.916
<i>Riri Williams always thinks she can
build her way out of her problems.</i>

226
00:16:25.500 --> 00:16:27.290
<i>And with this latest invention.</i>

227
00:16:27.291 --> 00:16:29.790
<i>you wouldn't blame her
for believing she can.</i>

228
00:16:29.791 --> 00:16:34.583
<i>More than a suit of armor. it's
a fusion of human and machine.</i>

229
00:16:35.166 --> 00:16:37.207
<i>elevating her to new
levels of consciousness</i>

230
00:16:37.208 --> 00:16:39.458
<i>no living person has ever known.</i>

231
00:16:41.291 --> 00:16:42.791
You'll be a human synthezoid.

232
00:16:43.333 --> 00:16:46.082
There's no telling how
that power will change you

233
00:16:46.083 --> 00:16:48.083
or if you can ever turn back.

234
00:16:48.791 --> 00:16:50.291
Growing up. I lost a lot.

235
00:16:50.833 --> 00:16:54.041
And then the world ended
and I lost everyone else.

236
00:16:54.916 --> 00:16:58.208
If this will help me take the
fight to Beck. I have to do it.

237
00:16:59.500 --> 00:17:00.791
<i>'Cause this fight...</i>

238
00:17:02.166 --> 00:17:03.500
<i>is all I have left.</i>

239
00:17:13.041 --> 00:17:16.208
[The Watcher] <i>But even with the powers
of the Vision flowing through her.</i>

240
00:17:17.125 --> 00:17:21.541
<i>she still can't see... that
this is how it ends for her.</i>

241
00:17:23.166 --> 00:17:24.250
Always.

242
00:17:33.333 --> 00:17:35.583
We are approaching
Beck's airspace.

243
00:17:41.000 --> 00:17:43.000
[Wong] Looks like a heavy
ground-to-air barrage.

244
00:17:44.166 --> 00:17:45.833
Guess that means
you're up. Riri.

245
00:17:47.375 --> 00:17:49.333
Are you ready for
this? What do you see?

246
00:17:55.333 --> 00:17:56.583
It's working. yeah.

247
00:17:59.833 --> 00:18:01.915
I can see what's
real and what's fake.

248
00:18:01.916 --> 00:18:03.875
Just stay on my wing
and you'll be fine.

249
00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:06.000
[whirring]

250
00:18:08.625 --> 00:18:09.625
[Riri] Fake!

251
00:18:10.833 --> 00:18:12.583
Fake! Fake!

252
00:18:14.583 --> 00:18:15.666
Fake!

253
00:18:21.416 --> 00:18:23.333
That's real! Light 'em up now!

254
00:18:29.166 --> 00:18:31.790
[groans] Whoa. whoa!

255
00:18:31.791 --> 00:18:33.290
- What?
- What's going on?

256
00:18:33.291 --> 00:18:34.540
Why are you slowing down?

257
00:18:34.541 --> 00:18:36.958
Something's off. My neural
network is sputtering.

258
00:18:38.791 --> 00:18:39.999
But I can fight through it.

259
00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:43.791
Come on. Riri. You can
do this. I know you can.

260
00:18:51.416 --> 00:18:54.291
- [explosion]
- [Riri Williams screaming]

261
00:18:55.875 --> 00:18:56.875
[Wong] Oh. oh. oh!

262
00:18:58.708 --> 00:19:00.875
[Riri Williams
continues screaming]

263
00:19:01.958 --> 00:19:02.958
[grunts]

264
00:19:06.541 --> 00:19:08.207
[Ying Nan] Riri. Riri!

265
00:19:08.208 --> 00:19:09.665
[screams]

266
00:19:09.666 --> 00:19:12.290
Come on. Are you with
me? What's your status?

267
00:19:12.291 --> 00:19:14.250
There's something wrong
with my neural network.

268
00:19:14.791 --> 00:19:16.250
I can't see through
the illusions.

269
00:19:16.833 --> 00:19:18.624
Can you still hack
the control hub?

270
00:19:18.625 --> 00:19:20.333
If we can actually
make it there.

271
00:19:21.208 --> 00:19:22.374
Where's the rest of the team?

272
00:19:22.375 --> 00:19:26.166
They're holding off Beck's forces to
give us a chance. but not for long.

273
00:19:29.083 --> 00:19:31.041
We need to finish this. Riri.

274
00:19:31.750 --> 00:19:32.750
[exhales]

275
00:19:35.083 --> 00:19:37.125
[panting]

276
00:19:39.250 --> 00:19:41.166
[distant explosions]

277
00:19:55.708 --> 00:19:57.082
[charging]

278
00:19:57.083 --> 00:19:58.375
[clanging]

279
00:20:11.041 --> 00:20:14.582
I've led you this far.
This is where you end it.

280
00:20:14.583 --> 00:20:16.666
[Riri Williams panting]

281
00:20:22.333 --> 00:20:23.750
Wireless connection's
still dead.

282
00:20:24.291 --> 00:20:25.625
Old-fashioned way it is.

283
00:20:26.708 --> 00:20:29.457
Just the fate of the literal
world at your fingertips.

284
00:20:29.458 --> 00:20:30.541
No presh.

285
00:20:31.375 --> 00:20:32.624
You might wanna take cover.

286
00:20:32.625 --> 00:20:33.958
This is about to get...

287
00:20:35.666 --> 00:20:37.208
What? No.

288
00:20:37.708 --> 00:20:40.916
No. no. no!

289
00:20:42.083 --> 00:20:43.541
No! Ying Nan!

290
00:20:44.875 --> 00:20:47.416
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

291
00:20:51.458 --> 00:20:52.875
[Beck laughing]

292
00:20:53.458 --> 00:20:54.958
Come on. Riri.

293
00:20:55.541 --> 00:20:57.708
You should know in this world.

294
00:20:58.750 --> 00:21:01.040
you can't trust anyone.

295
00:21:01.041 --> 00:21:03.499
No. this doesn't make any sense.

296
00:21:03.500 --> 00:21:06.374
We navigated the holograms.
followed the coordinates.

297
00:21:06.375 --> 00:21:08.375
The nanite network
should be here!

298
00:21:09.875 --> 00:21:10.958
And it is

299
00:21:11.625 --> 00:21:14.707
because I am the network.

300
00:21:14.708 --> 00:21:15.791
What the...

301
00:21:16.375 --> 00:21:18.457
You're not the first person

302
00:21:18.458 --> 00:21:22.958
to give themselves a
high-tech makeover. Riri.

303
00:21:24.750 --> 00:21:29.040
I had my nanites
uploaded into my body

304
00:21:29.041 --> 00:21:32.332
so I could control
all my illusions

305
00:21:32.333 --> 00:21:34.707
with the blink of an eye.

306
00:21:34.708 --> 00:21:37.415
So if you came to
take them from me.

307
00:21:37.416 --> 00:21:40.665
I'm afraid you're gonna
have to pluck them

308
00:21:40.666 --> 00:21:44.458
out of my cold dead body.

309
00:21:45.041 --> 00:21:47.375
By the looks of it. I won't
have to wait very long.

310
00:21:47.875 --> 00:21:50.165
The tech has come at a price.

311
00:21:50.166 --> 00:21:52.416
but it was worth it because now.

312
00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:57.457
you are all that
remains of the Alliance.

313
00:21:57.458 --> 00:21:59.666
No. These are all lies!

314
00:22:03.125 --> 00:22:06.916
Easy. Riri. I shut down
your phasing capabilities.

315
00:22:07.583 --> 00:22:10.375
I programmed Vision. remember?

316
00:22:10.875 --> 00:22:13.707
And from the moment you
brought his tech back online.

317
00:22:13.708 --> 00:22:17.749
I've allowed you
to do just enough

318
00:22:17.750 --> 00:22:19.290
to come right to me.

319
00:22:19.291 --> 00:22:21.375
- [electricity crackling]
- [screaming]

320
00:22:25.458 --> 00:22:27.415
Then why bring me here?

321
00:22:27.416 --> 00:22:31.624
So I can live to
enjoy my victory.

322
00:22:31.625 --> 00:22:34.749
I didn't think I had much
time left in this world

323
00:22:34.750 --> 00:22:40.082
until I saw this brilliant little
glow-up of yours and realized

324
00:22:40.083 --> 00:22:42.165
I don't need my body

325
00:22:42.166 --> 00:22:44.165
when I can have Vision's.

326
00:22:44.166 --> 00:22:45.749
[screaming louder]

327
00:22:45.750 --> 00:22:50.041
It'll be so much faster
if you don't fight. Riri.

328
00:22:51.250 --> 00:22:53.207
See? Almost done.

329
00:22:53.208 --> 00:22:56.750
It's too bad. I was starting to
feel like we had a connection.

330
00:22:57.875 --> 00:22:59.749
That's the thing
about connections.

331
00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:02.416
- They go both ways.
- [powering down]

332
00:23:03.416 --> 00:23:04.416
[grunting]

333
00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:09.833
[screaming]

334
00:23:11.625 --> 00:23:13.832
If you hadn't noticed.
I'm kind of stubborn.

335
00:23:13.833 --> 00:23:15.541
and I've come too
far to give up now.

336
00:23:17.666 --> 00:23:18.666
[Beck] Oh!

337
00:23:19.083 --> 00:23:20.583
But you will.

338
00:23:21.708 --> 00:23:22.708
[laughs]

339
00:23:24.416 --> 00:23:25.416
[screams]

340
00:23:30.625 --> 00:23:34.000
Beck. put away these magic
tricks and stop hiding!

341
00:23:36.208 --> 00:23:37.208
You're right.

342
00:23:39.416 --> 00:23:41.958
If my illusions
will not break you.

343
00:23:43.000 --> 00:23:46.333
perhaps the truth will.

344
00:23:48.416 --> 00:23:51.208
You never left the fields.

345
00:23:57.166 --> 00:23:58.166
[gasps]

346
00:24:02.291 --> 00:24:04.291
[sobbing]

347
00:24:05.583 --> 00:24:07.500
[Beck] Your team is dead.

348
00:24:08.666 --> 00:24:11.208
The Alliance is dead.

349
00:24:12.500 --> 00:24:14.541
You failed.

350
00:24:16.208 --> 00:24:18.416
You failed your friends.

351
00:24:20.333 --> 00:24:21.333
You...

352
00:24:22.083 --> 00:24:25.583
You have nothing
left to fight for.

353
00:24:27.625 --> 00:24:28.666
[The Watcher] <i>This is it.</i>

354
00:24:29.375 --> 00:24:31.583
The moment where it always ends.

355
00:24:32.291 --> 00:24:33.750
Her spirit is exhausted.

356
00:24:34.500 --> 00:24:37.833
<i>She's seen too
much. lost too much.</i>

357
00:24:38.541 --> 00:24:42.625
<i>Her will to fight is all Riri Williams
felt she had left in this world.</i>

358
00:24:43.166 --> 00:24:46.083
and now she's lost that. too.

359
00:24:49.125 --> 00:24:51.125
- [pulsing]
- [Riri Williams screams]

360
00:24:56.291 --> 00:24:58.666
[The Watcher]
<i>Finally. at the end.</i>

361
00:24:59.458 --> 00:25:01.291
<i>without any hope left.</i>

362
00:25:02.666 --> 00:25:03.833
<i>I just...</i>

363
00:25:04.625 --> 00:25:08.041
I don't know if I can bear
to watch it one more time.

364
00:25:13.041 --> 00:25:16.041
- Yes!
- [groaning. grunts]

365
00:25:24.458 --> 00:25:26.457
Oh. thatta girl. Riri.

366
00:25:26.458 --> 00:25:29.958
You don't have to
resist anymore.

367
00:25:36.541 --> 00:25:37.583
No.

368
00:25:45.541 --> 00:25:46.750
Fight.

369
00:25:48.875 --> 00:25:49.916
<i>Riri.</i>

370
00:25:50.666 --> 00:25:51.666
<i>Fight.</i>

371
00:25:52.250 --> 00:25:54.250
<i>- Fight back.</i>
- [panting]

372
00:25:56.875 --> 00:25:58.541
[crackling]

373
00:25:58.958 --> 00:25:59.958
What?

374
00:26:04.958 --> 00:26:06.958
What... What's happening?

375
00:26:12.041 --> 00:26:13.875
[gasps] No. no!

376
00:26:15.541 --> 00:26:17.499
No. no. no. no!

377
00:26:17.500 --> 00:26:19.291
No. no. what are you doing?

378
00:26:24.250 --> 00:26:25.790
Finishing this.

379
00:26:25.791 --> 00:26:27.625
I beat you!

380
00:26:28.208 --> 00:26:29.458
[screaming]

381
00:26:34.083 --> 00:26:36.166
No! No. no. no. no!

382
00:26:37.958 --> 00:26:39.125
My nanites!

383
00:26:40.166 --> 00:26:41.540
[gasps. coughs]

384
00:26:41.541 --> 00:26:43.083
[gasping heavily]

385
00:26:45.875 --> 00:26:47.707
I see through your reality.

386
00:26:47.708 --> 00:26:50.125
No. no. no. [coughs]

387
00:26:54.500 --> 00:26:55.750
And I'm shutting it down.

388
00:26:56.333 --> 00:27:00.124
I am the master of illusions!

389
00:27:00.125 --> 00:27:04.915
I can make it like your
little victory never happened.

390
00:27:04.916 --> 00:27:08.124
The people will never know.

391
00:27:08.125 --> 00:27:11.458
They will because I'm going to
give them a vision of the future.

392
00:27:13.333 --> 00:27:14.625
With what?

393
00:27:15.375 --> 00:27:16.416
Hope.

394
00:27:28.708 --> 00:27:29.708
No.

395
00:27:30.791 --> 00:27:33.041
No. No.

396
00:27:42.125 --> 00:27:43.458
[people cheering]

397
00:27:45.416 --> 00:27:46.416
[thudding]

398
00:27:48.208 --> 00:27:49.208
[gasping]

399
00:27:55.375 --> 00:27:56.375
[gurgles]

400
00:28:12.375 --> 00:28:16.750
[The Eminence] What has he done?

401
00:28:17.500 --> 00:28:20.915
[The Incarnate] He has
broken his oath. Again.

402
00:28:20.916 --> 00:28:23.708
[The Executioner] We
cannot allow this to stand.

403
00:28:24.291 --> 00:28:25.291
No.

404
00:28:25.791 --> 00:28:28.666
So from here on. we must
continue to watch...

405
00:28:30.208 --> 00:28:31.291
him.

406
00:28:35.333 --> 00:28:38.333
[♪ upbeat instrumental
music playing]

406
00:28:39.305 --> 00:29:39.231
